description: TEHRAN – Russian Security Council's secretary Sergei Shoigu said on Tuesday that his country has nearly completed the required procedures to sign a new bilateral treaty with Iran soon, the TASS news agency reported.

description: TEHRAN - The spokesperson for Iranian Ministry of Foreign Affairs has denounced the European Troika's decision to impose sanctions on Iran over unsubstantial allegations of Tehran’s alleged missile provision to Russia.

description: TEHRAN - Iran earned a hard-fought 1-0 win against United Arab of Emirates in their AFC Asian Qualifiers – Road to 26 Group A tie on Tuesday.

description: TEHRAN- Tehran hosted a seminar on analyzing U.S. foreign policy and the November presidential election.

description: TEHRAN- Ulterior motives lurking behind the screening of a documentary that unveils leaked footage of the Israeli police questioning Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu have come to the fore.
title: Behind The Bibi Files

description: TEHRAN - "The Bibi Files" is not merely a documentary; it's a harrowing exposé, a cinematic indictment of a man who, for over a decade, held Israel in his iron grip. It's a story of ambition unchecked, of political gamesmanship masquerading as statesmanship, and ultimately, of a society fractured by the relentless pursuit of power.
title: The House of Cards: The Rise and Fall of Benjamin Netanyahu

description: TEHRAN - A recent report by the German state-owned broadcaster Deutsche Welle revealed that Germany covers 30% of Israel’s arms imports, with the United States and Germany being the two major suppliers of weapons to the Israeli regime.

description: TEHRAN- The Iranian deputy head of Legal and International Affairs for the foreign ministry has asserted that the International Court of Justice (ICJ) has identified the Zionist regime as accountable for acts of discrimination and apartheid against the Palestinian people.

description: TEHRAN- Rear Admiral Shahram Irani, the Iranian Army Navy commander has declared that Tehran is unafraid to confront any regional or external powers in the Persian Gulf.

description: TEHRAN- The secretary of Iran’s National Security Council is in Russia to attend the 14th Meeting of BRICS High-Ranking Officials responsible for security matters in St. Petersburg.

description: TEHRAN- The Saudi Arabian Minister of Interior congratulated Eskandar Momeni on his recent appointment as the Minister of Interior of Iran through a formal message.

description: TEHRAN – Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian has extended his congratulations to the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK) on the occasion of its 76th founding anniversary.

description: TEHRAN - It's become a familiar ritual, this frantic scrolling through the endless feed of news updates. The world, it seems, is a whirlwind of events, each headline vying for attention, each story competing for our fleeting interest. But sometimes, amidst the chaos, a particular issue catches our eye, a narrative that pulls us in, demanding deeper understanding. Today, I find myself drawn to a story unfolding in the heart of West Asia, a story of political paralysis of an unlawful entity struggling to find its footing in a world of ever-shifting sands: The story of the Zionist regime, and its Sisyphean task of finding a stable government.
title: The Sisyphean task: Why Israel's political landscape remains stuck in a cycle of gridlock

description: TEHRAN – The UK, Germany, France, and the United States are preparing to impose new sanctions against Iran, accusing the West Asian country of supplying Russia with missiles for use in the Ukraine war.

description: TEHRAN - Imagine a world where a simple DNA test, coupled with the power of artificial intelligence (AI), could predict your risk of developing cancer. This isn’t science fiction anymore. Researchers are harnessing the power of AI to analyze genetic data, potentially paving the way for personalized cancer prevention and early detection.
title: From genes to therapy: AI predicts your cancer risk with a DNA swab

description: I will not hide from you that I suffer from anxiety. Like most humanitarian workers, I can’t sleep. I can’t have sound, uninterrupted sleep as a result of the fear. Fear haunts us in every step. I am one of the founders of the Wefaq Association. Since 2010, the most important work we do is provide protection, economic, legal and psychological support, for women who have been victims of violence and for children at risk.
title: Gaza is hell for aid workers – and it is doubly difficult if you are a woman

description: TEHRAN-Since the creation of comic books in the midst of the Great Depression in the 1930s, superheroes have been used to entertain and inspire readers, as well as to address important events. During the Depression, they were a symbol of hope for a better world. As the United States entered World War II, superheroes encouraged soldiers on the battlefield and united the public by praising patriotic ideals and mocking their enemies.
title: Heroes of the age of terror: what happened to American superheroes on 9/11?  Part 1
